e-hailing drivers from Uber and Bolt say too much of their commission is taken and their fares are driven down. eNCA/Monique Mortlock JOHANNESBURG - E-hailing drivers are set for a massive three-day protest next week. Drivers affiliated with global app giants like Uber, Bolt, inDriver and Uber Eats are calling on government to assist them. READ: E-hailing drivers protesting outside Parliament They say they need help to curb exploitation by their app partners. Drivers add that the petrol price has been increasing but app companies refuse to adjust the prices.